Constructor Detail

DataStructureUtil

protected DataStructureUtil()
Default constructor for this class. Having the constructor be protected is a special form of the Singleton Creational Pattern. This prevents other class from instantiating an instance. It allows the class loader to load the class when a reference to one this class's static methods is made. However, if a class wishes to extend this class, then an instance of this class is created for each instance of the subclass.
